        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 13 at 1:28PM MDT by NWS El Paso Tx/Santa Teresa NM</headline>
        <description>At 128 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 4
miles south of Cloudcroft, moving northeast at 5 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Sacramento, Cloudcroft, Sunspot, Mountain Park, Benson Ridge, Hay
Canyon, Cox Canyon, Karr Canyon, Dry Canyon, James Canyon, High
Nogal, Bluff Springs, Upper Karr Canyon, and Piney Woods.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
